problems.solution:
Iterating over all fields with an array counter is a classic awk pattern.

```awk
{
    for (i = 1; i <= NF; i++)
        count[$i]++
}
END {
    PROCINFO["sorted_in"] = "@ind_str_asc"
    for (w in count)
        print w, count[w]
}
```

**Explanation:**
- `for (i = 1; i <= NF; i++)` iterates over every field on the current line.
- `count[$i]++` uses the field value as an array key and increments the count.
- `PROCINFO["sorted_in"] = "@ind_str_asc"` (gawk) makes `for (w in count)` iterate in ascending string order.
- This is a general-purpose word-counting skeleton useful in many data-processing tasks.

